Hi Folks,

I’ve written a version of Ocaml’s Graphics module which outputs PDF 
directly, using the CamlPDF library - its only dependency. It’s based on 
the approach of Pierre Weis’ GraphPS program.

It has the same API as Ocaml’s module - just have your build process 
find the GraphPDF files before it finds the system ones - the vast 
majority of programs shouldn’t need altering.

http://www.coherentpdf.com/graphpdf-1.0.tar.bz2

Cheers,

-- 
John Whitington
Director, Coherent Graphics Ltd
http://www.coherentpdf.com/

